<div class="overflow-hidden p-50 editorial">
<h2>Flex Layout Examples</h2>

<h3>Golden Ratio</h3>

<p><code>gmajor</code> and <code>gminor</code> classes represent the larger and smaller portion of the golden ratio, respectively.</p>

<div class="flex flex-wrap justify-stretch -mx-10 mb-50">
  {% for w in ['gminor','gmajor','gmajor','gminor'] %}
  <div class="p-10 flex-{{ w }}">
    <div class="p-10 bg-yellow-100 ">
      .flex-{{ w }}
    </div>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>

<h3>Thirds</h3>

<p>Because thirds are an irrational number, the <code>2/3</code> and <code>1/3</code> are rounded up and down respecively. There is an alternalte <code>1/3-up</code> which is rounded up -- this is best used in combination with two <code>1/3</code> blocks, as below.</p>

<div class="flex flex-wrap justify-stretch -mx-10 mb-50">
  {% for w in ['1/3','2/3','1/3','1/3-up','1/3'] %}
  <div class="p-10 flex-{{ w }}">
    <div class="p-10 bg-yellow-100 ">
      .flex-{{ w }}
    </div>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>

<h3>Flex Layout: Quarters</h3>

<p>You can get a 50% space by using either <code>1/2</code> or <code>2/4</code>.</p>

<div class="flex flex-wrap -mx-10 mb-50">
  {% for w in ['3/4','1/4','1/4','1/2','1/4', '2/4', '1/2'] %}
  <div class="p-10 flex-{{ w }}">
    <div class="p-10 bg-yellow-100 ">
      .flex-{{ w }}
    </div>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>

<h3>Flex Layout: Fifths</h3>

<p>There are very few pieces of content that fit comfortably in a <code>1/5</code> space.</p>
  
<div class="flex flex-wrap -mx-10 mb-50">
  {% for w in ['4/5','1/5','3/5','2/5'] %}
  <div class="p-10 flex-{{ w }}">
    <div class="p-10 bg-yellow-100 ">
      .flex-{{ w }}
    </div>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>

</div>